typeDescription: Model information for a subsidiary object used to support the daily running of experiment and the laboratory.

fields.name: Name
fields.description: Name of this Object.

fields.name: ID
fields.description: ID of this Object.

fields.name: Object
fields.description: Object of this Object.

metadata.value: The object reference of this object.

fields.name: Type
fields.description: Type of this Object.

fields.name: Notebook
fields.description: Notebook this object belongs to.

fields.name: Objects
fields.description: Objects that represent instances of this model.

fields.name: Deprecated
fields.description: Indicates if this item model is historical and no longer used in the lab.

fields.name: Authors
fields.description: The person who created this item model.

fields.name: Synonyms
fields.description: List of possible alternative names this model goes by.

fields.name: UNII
fields.description: Unique Ingredient Identifier of compounds based on the unified identification scheme of FDA.

fields.name: InstrumentSchematics
fields.description: Detailed drawings of the instrument that explain its capabilities and limitations.

fields.name: ImageFile
fields.description: A photo of this model of container.

fields.name: ImageFileScale
fields.description: The scale relating pixels of ImageFile to real world distance.

fields.name: PreferredCamera
fields.description: Indicates the recommended camera type for taking an image of an object of this model.

fields.name: FluidTransport
fields.description: Indicates that this item is stored in a storage buffer and will be wet when retrieved from storage.

fields.name: Expires
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model expire after a given amount of time.

fields.name: ShelfLife
fields.description: The length of time after DateCreated that items of this model are recommended for use before they should be discarded.

fields.name: UnsealedShelfLife
fields.description: The length of time after DateUnsealed that items of this model are recommended for use before they should be discarded.

fields.name: LightSensitive
fields.description: Determines if the item reacts or degrades in the presence of light and should be stored in the dark to avoid exposure.

fields.name: DefaultStorageCondition
fields.description: The condition in which items of this model are stored when not in use by an experiment; this condition may be overridden by the specific storage condition of any given item.

fields.name: TransportChilled
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model should be refrigerated during transport when used in experiments.

fields.name: TransportWarmed
fields.description: The temperature that items of this model should be incubated at while transported between instruments during experimentation.

fields.name: Connectors
fields.description: Specifications for the ends of this plumbing component that may connect to other plumbing components or instrument ports.

fields.name: Size
fields.description: The length of this item, in the direction of fluid flow.

fields.name: DeadVolume
fields.description: The fluid volume that can be contained in this item component when used as part of the plumbing.

fields.name: FluidCategory
fields.description: Type of fluids that can be used with this item component when used as part of the plumbing.

fields.name: WiringConnectors
fields.description: Specifications for the ends of the wiring connectors on this Item model that may plug into and conductively connect to other items, parts or instruments.

fields.name: WiringLength
fields.description: The length of this item, in the direction of the electricity flow.

fields.name: WiringDiameters
fields.description: For each member of WiringConnectors, its effective conductive diameter.

fields.name: Dimensions
fields.description: The external dimensions of this model of item in it's packaged form.

fields.name: Footprint
fields.description: Standard form factor of the exterior bottom portion of this model of item used to seat the item in an open position.

fields.name: MaterialDimensions
fields.description: The actual dimensions of this material in it's unpackaged form.

fields.name: CuttableWidth
fields.description: Indicates if this items length can but cut lengthwise, decreasing the width of the item.

fields.name: CuttableLength
fields.description: Indicates if this items length can but cut crosswise, decreasing the length of the item.

fields.name: ProductDocumentationFiles
fields.description: PDFs of any product documentation provided by the supplier of this item model.

fields.name: Products
fields.description: Products ordering information for this model of part.

fields.name: KitProducts
fields.description: Products ordering information for this model if this model is part of one or more kits.

fields.name: MixedBatchProducts
fields.description: Products ordering information for this model if this model is part of one or more mixed batches.

fields.name: ServiceProviders
fields.description: Service companies that provide synthesis of this model as a service.

fields.name: RentByDefault
fields.description: Indicates if this item should be 'rented' from the ECL rather than purchased when it is needed during the course of an experiment.

fields.name: PreferredWashBin
fields.description: Indicates the recommended bin for dishwashing this container.

fields.name: WettedMaterials
fields.description: The materials of which this part is made that may come in direct contact with fluids.

fields.name: IncompatibleMaterials
fields.description: A list of materials that would be damaged if wetted by this model.

fields.name: LiquidHandlerIncompatible
fields.description: Indicates if this item cannot be reliably aspirated or dispensed on an automated liquid handling robot.

fields.name: Sterile
fields.description: Indicates that this model of item arrives sterile from the manufacturer.

fields.name: Sterilized
fields.description: Indicates if this model of item is sterilized by autoclaving upon receiving and, if it is reusable, after being cleaned before it is reused.

fields.name: SterilizationBag
fields.description: Indicates if this model of item is sealed in an autoclave bag before autoclaving. The bag protects its sterility until it is used.

fields.name: NucleaseFree
fields.description: Indicates if this model of item is tested to be not contaminated with DNase and RNase by the manufacturer.

fields.name: NucleicAcidFree
fields.description: Indicates if this model of item is tested to be not contaminated with DNA and RNA by the manufacturer.

fields.name: PyrogenFree
fields.description: Indicates if this model of item is tested to be not contaminated with endotoxin by the manufacturer.

fields.name: Radioactive
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model emit substantial ionizing radiation.

fields.name: Ventilated
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model must be handled in a ventilated enclosures.

fields.name: Flammable
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model are easily set aflame under standard conditions.

fields.name: Acid
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model are strong acids (pH <= 2) and require dedicated secondary containment during storage.

fields.name: Base
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model are strong bases (pH >= 12) and require dedicated secondary containment during storage.

fields.name: Pyrophoric
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model can ignite spontaneously upon exposure to air.

fields.name: WaterReactive
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model react spontaneously upon exposure to water.

fields.name: Fuming
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model emit fumes spontaneously when exposed to air.

fields.name: Aqueous
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model are a solution in water.

fields.name: HazardousBan
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model are currently banned from usage in the ECL because the facility isn't yet equiped to handle them.

fields.name: ExpirationHazard
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model become hazardous once they are expired and therefore must be automatically disposed of when they pass their expiration date.

fields.name:
ParticularlyHazardous
Substance
fields.description: Indicates if special precautions should be taken in handling this substance as indicated by the MSDS classification.

fields.name: DrainDisposal
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model may be safely disposed down a standard drain.

fields.name: MSDSRequired
fields.description: Indicates if an MSDS is applicable for this model.

fields.name: MSDSFile
fields.description: PDF of the models MSDS (Materials Saftey Data Sheet).

fields.name: NFPA
fields.description: The National Fire Protection Association (NFPA) 704 hazard diamond classification for the substance.

fields.name: DOTHazardClass
fields.description: The Department of Transportation hazard classification of the substance.

fields.name: BiosafetyLevel
fields.description: The Biosafety classification of the substance.

fields.name: MaintenanceFrequency
fields.description: A list of the maintenance models for this part model and their required frequencies.

fields.name: QualificationFrequency
fields.description: A list of the Qualification models for this part model and their required frequencies.

fields.name: SupportedInstruments
fields.description: A list of instruments for which this model is replacement part or an accompanying accessory.

fields.name: CleaningMethod
fields.description: Indicates the type of cleaning that is employed for this part before reuse.

fields.name: ContinuousOperation
fields.description: Indicates if the item is required to operate continuously in the lab, regardless of if it is InUse by a specific protocol.

fields.name: MaxNumberOfHours
fields.description: The amount of time this item can be used during experiments before performance is expected to degrade and the item should be replaced.

fields.name: MaxNumberOfUses
fields.description: The maximum number of uses for which this item is expected to perform before performance is expected to degrade and the item should be replaced.

fields.name: Density
fields.description: Known density of items of this model at room temperature.

fields.name: pH
fields.description: The logarithmic concentration of hydrogen ions of the substance at room temperature.

fields.name: ExtinctionCoefficients
fields.description: A measure of how strongly this chemical absorbs light at a particular wavelength.

fields.name: State
fields.description: The physical state of the item when well solvated at room temperature and pressure.

fields.name: Reusability
fields.description: Indicates that this item can be used repeatedly.

fields.name: Protocols
fields.description: All protocols that used this item at any point during their execution in the lab.

fields.name: Preparable
fields.description: Indicates if items of this model may be prepared as needed during the course of an experiment.
